HEADWORD: clammyweed
<hw>clammyweed</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>strong-scented herb
(<spn>Polanisia graveolens</spn>) common in the southern U. S. covered
with intermixed gland and hairs.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> <spn>Polanisia graveolens</spn>, Polanisia
dodecandra.</syn>⟦br⟧
